Jigawa state has recorded 51 new cases of COVID-19, making a total number of confirmed cases in the state to 169, and 3 deaths recorded so far. The commissioner of Health, who is also the chairman task force on COVID-19, Dr Abba Zakari Confirmed this to Newsmen, at the NYSC orientation camp, Dutse, added that preventive measures are been taken to curtail the spread of the pandemic which include imposing of wearing face masks, observing social distance, washing of hands among others. According to him, 31 of the cases are almajiri that were repatriated from Kano state, which accounts for 56 percent of the total log of cases recorded in the state, adding that government is taking adequate care of the returnee Almajiri in terms of their feeding, shelter and other basic needs. Meanwhile, the Commissioner explained that testing will soon commence in Jigawa, as they have already procured the equipments and have decided to use the Dutse General hospital’s laboratory for the testing. “The testing centre will ease difficulty faced in taking samples to Abuja and Kaduna”. He noted. Vanguard By Aliyu Dangida - Dutse Jigawa state has recorded 51 new cases of Coronavirus, making a total number of confirmed cases in the state to 169, and 3 deaths recorded so far. The commissioner of Health, who is also the chairman task force on Covid-19, Dr Abba Zakari Confirmed this… May 14, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" The Jigawa State Commissioner for Health, Dr. Abba Zakari, on Thursday, confirmed the first COVID-19 death in the state. Zakari, who is also the Chairman of the state Task Force on COVID-19, said at a press briefing in Dutse the patient died in Dutse local government area of the state.… April 30, 2020 In "News" Governor Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State yesterday berated his Kaduna State counterpart, Governor Nasir El-Rufai, asking him to stop politicizing the issue of almajiris evacuated to the state who tested positive to COVID-19. May 11, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"